{"word":"G26 - ἀγάπη - agápē - ag-ah'-pay - Charity","slug":"G26","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀγάπη</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>agápē"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ag-ah'-pay"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Charity"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x0313;&#x03B3;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03C0;&#x03B7; - agape&#x0304;</b> - <i>ag-ah'-pay</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G25\">G25</a>; <i>love</i>, that is, <i>affection</i> or <i>benevolence</i>; specifically (plural) a <i>love feast:</i> - (feast of) charity ([-ably]), dear, love."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G25\">G25</a>, <a href=\"#/G27\">G27</a>"}]}